---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
const pageTitle = "Shaurya Srivastav | Works";
---
<Layout pageTitle={pageTitle}>
    <div class="gif">
        <img width="300" height="259" alt="Laptop Animation" src="/laptop.webp"/>
    </div>
    <h1>Explore My Projects</h1>
    <p>
        Welcome to my collection of projects! While these are some of my earlier works, you'll find my latest and greatest projects on my <a href="https://github.com/Shaurya-Srivastav" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub profile</a>. Dive in to see how I bring ideas to life through code and innovation.
    </p>
    
    <div class="github-link">
        <a href="https://github.com/Shaurya-Srivastav" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
            <img 
                width="100" 
                height="100" 
                alt="GitHub Icon" 
                src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/devicons/devicon/icons/github/github-original.svg" 
                style="width: 100px; height: 100px;"/>
        </a>
        <p>Visit my GitHub to explore all my projects!</p>
    </div>

    <h2>My Tech Stack</h2>
    <p>
        Here's a glimpse into the technologies I work with. From machine learning to cloud computing, I leverage a diverse set of tools to build impactful solutions.
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Machine Learning:</strong> NumPy, PyTorch, TensorFlow, Matplotlib, Pandas, Scikit-learn, HuggingFace, Apache Spark</li>
        <li><strong>Cloud:</strong> Google Cloud Platform (GCP), AWS (EC2, S3, Lambda), Firebase, MongoDB Atlas, Docker, Kubernetes, CI/CD with GitHub Actions</li>
        <li><strong>Languages:</strong> Python, Java, C/C++, JavaScript (ES6+), TypeScript, HTML5, CSS3, SQL, Bash/Shell Scripting</li>
        <li><strong>Frameworks & Libraries:</strong> ReactJS, AngularJS, NodeJS, Flask, Express.js</li>
        <li><strong>Databases:</strong> MySQL, PostgreSQL, MongoDB</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
        These technologies empower me to develop full-stack applications, implement robust machine learning models, and manage scalable cloud infrastructures.
    </p>

    <h2>My Certifications</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>IBM AI Engineering Professional Certificate</li>
        <li>Google Cloud NEXT 2023 - Student Innovator</li>
        <li>AI-ML Ops Engineer Quizathon</li>
        <li>Introduction to Generative AI</li>
        <li>Cloud Architect Quizathon</li>
        <li>Data Professional Quizathon</li>
        <li>Application Developer Quizathon</li>
        <li>DevOps Engineer Quizathon</li>
        <li>Productivity Developer Quizathon</li>
        <li>Generative AI Fundamentals</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
        My certifications demonstrate my commitment to continuous learning and expertise in various domains of technology, from artificial intelligence to cloud architecture.
    </p>

    <h2>My Courses</h2>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Machine Learning:</strong> ECS 289L - Advanced Deep Learning, ECS 171 - Machine Learning, ECS 174 - Computer Vision, MAT 131A - Probability Theory</li>
        <li><strong>Algorithm Design:</strong> ECS 120 - Theory of Computation, ECS 122A - Algorithm Design & Analysis, ECS 36C - Algorithms and Data Structures, ECS 36B - Object Oriented Programming</li>
        <li><strong>Other:</strong> ECS 154A - Computer Architecture, ECS 165A - Database Systems, ECS 140A - Theory of Programming Languages</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
        These courses have provided me with a solid theoretical foundation and practical skills in computer science, enabling me to tackle complex problems and develop innovative solutions.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact Me</h2>
    <p>
        Feel free to reach out through <a href="mailto:ssrivastav@ucdavis.edu">email</a> or connect with me on <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/shauryasrivastav/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">LinkedIn</a>.
    </p>

    <div class="github-link">
        <a href="https://github.com/Shaurya-Srivastav" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
            <img 
                width="100" 
                height="100" 
                alt="GitHub Icon" 
                src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/devicons/devicon/icons/github/github-original.svg" 
                style="width: 100px; height: 100px;"/>
        </a>
        <p>Check out all my projects on GitHub!</p>
    </div>

    <style>
        /* Existing CSS */
        /* small */
        small {
            background-color: #584966;
            color: #fdebf3;
            border-radius: 6px;
            font-family: "Josefin Sans", sans-serif;
            font-weight: 600;
            padding: 0.3em 0.6em 0.2em;
        }

        /* Button */
        button {
            background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);
            border: 2px solid #78c2ad;
            border-radius: 8px;
            color: #78c2ad;
            font:
                600 16px "Josefin Sans",
                sans-serif;
            padding: 8px 16px;
            transition:
                background-color 0.4s,
                color 0.4s;
        }

        button:hover {
            background-color: #78c2ad;
            color: #fdebf3;
            cursor: pointer;
        }

        .button {
            text-align: center;
        }

        /* Skill images */
        .link-images img {
            margin: 16px 4px;
        }

        .github-link {
            text-align: center;
            margin: 2em 0;
        }

        .github-link img {
            transition: transform 0.3s;
        }

        .github-link img:hover {
            transform: scale(1.1);
        }

        .github-link p {
            margin-top: 0.5em;
            font-size: 1.1em;
            color: #555;
        }

        @media only screen and (max-width: 600px) {
            .link-images img {
                height: 30px;
                width: 30px;
                margin: 16px 1px;
            }

            .github-link img {
                width: 80px;
                height: 80px;
            }

            .github-link p {
                font-size: 1em;
            }
        }
    </style>
</Layout>
